In this op-ed article, Dr. Jill Biden discusses the importance of community colleges in the United States. As a teacher and community college instructor herself, she emphasizes the power of these institutions to change lives and provide opportunities for students. Dr. Biden mentions that President Obama recognizes the critical role community colleges play in the nation's economic recovery and has asked her to convene a summit of community college leaders at the White House. The article also highlights the upcoming regional community college summits, starting with one in Philadelphia, which aim to support community colleges' efforts in training programs, partnerships, and technology-driven learning. Dr. Biden mentions the $2 billion Trade Adjustment Assistance Community College and Career Training Grant Program, which will provide funding to support the development of postsecondary educational programs. She concludes by emphasizing the importance of community colleges in providing opportunities for students to build a more secure future and fulfill America's promise of opportunity for all.